snippet.title: In Delhi, 3 Crores In Old Notes, Packed To Cheat Airport X-Ray Machines

localized.description:
Over Rs. 3 crore in banned currency have been found in a raid on a hotel in Delhi's Karol Bagh. Officials of the Income Tax department and the Delhi Police jointly raided the hotel after a tip-off. Five people have been caught. The money, say the police, belongs to Mumbai-based Hawala operators.
